The SSE connection at `/api/exception-badge-updates` connects, receives the initial `count-update` event, then the stream goes idle (no exception count changes happening). A corporate reverse proxy (nginx/F5) detects the idle connection and closes it, triggering the frontend error handler. The error handler uses `console.error`, which causes Playwright E2E tests to fail (the `vuln-lense.spec.ts` test asserts zero console errors). After 5 retries with exponential backoff, the badge gives up and stays at 0.

